=E2=80=9D with a beautiful video about forgiveness. And on Monday, the comp=
any=E2=80=99s new CEO Connor Gaydos unveiled the Enron Egg, a portable nucl=
ear reactor for families everywhere.=20
If this were a real story, it would be one of the most important we=E2=80=
=99ve covered in the Weekly Dose. Imagine limitless safe, clean power in ev=
ery home! But it=E2=80=99s not real, so it=E2=80=99s down here in the Bonus=
 slot.=20
Gaydos, the internet genius behind the =E2=80=9CBirds Aren=E2=80=99t Real=
=E2=80=9D meme, bought the Enron trademark on the cheap a few years back. H=
e=E2=80=99s using it to engage in one of the best pieces of internet perfor=
mance art I=E2=80=99ve seen in a while. Check out this Houston Chronicle st=
ory and interview with Gaydos [ https://substack.com/redirect/07484783-a97f=
-4cc9-8d6a-70221b1ec344?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbq=
Osa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. The author knows the whole thing is a joke, but isn=E2=
=80=99t quite sure, and Gaydos sticks to the bit the whole time.=20
Typically in the Dose, we celebrate the technical ingenuity that produces w=
onders like the Egg. But it=E2=80=99s fun to celebrate the creative genius =
that completely makes it up, too.=20
