irect/33970b45-f960-446e-8435-db9121333c3a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] podcast had on me. I also wrote that J=
esse Michels is =E2=80=9Cmy only true must-watch.=E2=80=9D=20
Since then, The Telepathy Tapes has only grown in popularity. I=E2=80=99ve =
heard from so many people about the profound impact the podcast had on them=
=2E There have also, of course, been th=
e skeptics, who have nitpicked test pr=
otocols, dredged up old arguments against facilitated communication and ext=
ended them to spelling, and, in my opinion, completely missed the forest fo=
r the trees.=20
One of my favorite things about Jesse=E2=80=99s podcast is his combination =
of open-mindedness and rigor: willing to explore anywhere the data and expe=
rience lead, but not a wide-eyed believer.=20
Imagine my joy, then, when I saw Jesse tweet this [ https://substack.com/re=
direct/5f5eb9f9-a89b-4287-a690-085d6f29276f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7G=
nA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]:=20
=E2=80=9CThis is not intellectual entertainment. This is a paradigm shift.=
=E2=80=9D=20
I agree. Jesse has been instrumental in bringing it about =E2=80=94 I think=
 his is the most important channel on the internet =E2=80=94 and The Telepa=
thy Tapes seems to have pushed it over a line and into the national convers=
ation. Watching those worlds collide in this two-hour interview was delight=
ful. =20
It=E2=80=99s filled with spoilers, though, so you really should listen to T=
he Telepathy Tapes first:=20
